{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing mandatory IE validation in E1AP successful outcomes\n\n### Summary\nThe E1AP decoder was not validating mandatory information elements in successful outcome messages, causing downstream functions to generate outgoing signaling messages with missing mandatory fields. This led to rejected messages at the peer node.\n\nThis fix adds proper validation of mandatory IEs in successful outcomes.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap_common.c`: Enhanced `e1ap_decode_successful_outcome()` to validate presence of mandatory information elements for all supported procedure codes\n- Added checks for TransactionID in GNB-CU-UP-E1SetupResponse\n- Added checks for UE IDs and System-BearerContextSetupResponse in BearerContextSetupResponse\n- Added checks for UE IDs in BearerContextModificationResponse and BearerContextReleaseComplete\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder high load conditions with many E1AP transactions, peer nodes would reject outgoing messages due to missing mandatory IEs. Error logs showed \"Missing mandatory IE\" errors in the peer node traces. Memory usage remained stable but signaling success rates dropped significantly.\n"
}